<subSubSection pageId="68" pageNumber="69" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="68.[151,1436,438,643]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,438,463]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Chelicerae without intermarginal denticles; ventral opisthosoma pale in colour (
<figureCitation box="[1184,1284,438,462]" captionStart="FIGURE 58" captionStartId="90.[151,250,1810,1833]" captionTargetBox="[260,1377,264,1777]" captionTargetId="figure-62@90.[208,1378,229,1778]" captionTargetPageId="90" captionText="FIGURE 58. Habitus of species of the doriae group. (a–b) Eusparassus doriae (Simon, 1874) syntype female from Iran; (c) Eusparassus maynardi (Pocock, 1901) lectotype female from Pakistan; (d) Eusparassus fuscimanus Denis, 1958 female from Afghanistan; (e–f) Eusparassus oculatus (Kroneberg, 1875) female from Uzbekistan." pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Fig. 58b</figureCitation>
); ST small in size and located behind EM (e.g. 
<figureCitation box="[525,621,474,498]" captionStart="FIGURE 67" captionStartId="99.[151,250,1489,1512]" captionTargetBox="[172,1417,198,1468]" captionTargetId="figure-47@99.[151,1436,193,1469]" captionTargetPageId="99" captionText="FIGURE 67. Eusparassus doriae group. (a–b) Eusparassus doriae (Simon, 1874); (c–d) Eusparassus fuscimanus Denis, 1958; (e–f) Eusparassus kronebergi Denis, 1958. (a, c, e) left male palps, ventral; (b, d, f) epigynes, dorsal." pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Fig. 67a</figureCitation>
); AMLL of epigyne not fused anteriorly (e.g. 
<figureCitation box="[1136,1233,474,498]" captionStart="FIGURE 67" captionStartId="99.[151,250,1489,1512]" captionTargetBox="[172,1417,198,1468]" captionTargetId="figure-47@99.[151,1436,193,1469]" captionTargetPageId="99" captionText="FIGURE 67. Eusparassus doriae group. (a–b) Eusparassus doriae (Simon, 1874); (c–d) Eusparassus fuscimanus Denis, 1958; (e–f) Eusparassus kronebergi Denis, 1958. (a, c, e) left male palps, ventral; (b, d, f) epigynes, dorsal." pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Fig. 67b</figureCitation>
); GP present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="68.[151,1436,438,643]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,447,510,535]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Species composition.</emphasis>
Seven species: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Simon, 1874)" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[632,1033,510,534]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doriae">
<emphasis box="[632,856,510,534]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Eusparassus doriae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Simon, E." box="[873,1025,510,534]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="243 - 279" refId="ref52485" refString="Simon, E. (1874) Etudes arachnologiques. 3 e memoire. V. Revision des especes europeennes de la famille des Sparassidae. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, Paris, 5 (4), 243 - 279." type="journal article" year="1874">Simon, 1874</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kroneberg, 1875)" baseAuthorityName="Kroneberg" baseAuthorityYear="1875" box="[1047,1397,510,534]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculatus">
<emphasis box="[1047,1175,510,534]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">E. oculatus</emphasis>
(Kroneberg, 1875)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="(Simon, 1895)" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1895" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="potanini">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">E. potanini</emphasis>
(Simon, 1895)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pocock, 1901)" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[426,743,546,571]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maynardi">
<emphasis box="[426,563,547,571]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">E. maynardi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pocock, R. I." box="[577,735,546,570]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="478 - 498" refId="ref52017" refString="Pocock, R. I. (1901) Descriptions of some new species of spiders from British India. Journal of Bombay Natural History Society, 13, 478 - 498." type="journal article" year="1901">Pocock, 1901</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Denis, 1958" authorityName="Denis" authorityYear="1958" box="[754,1050,546,571]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kronebergi">
<emphasis box="[754,906,547,571]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">E. kronebergi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Denis, J." box="[912,1050,546,570]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="81 - 120" refId="ref50398" refString="Denis, J. (1958) Araignees (Araneidea) de l'Afghanistan. I. Videnskabelige Meddelelser fra Dansk naturhistorike Forenning, 120, 81 - 120." type="journal article" year="1958">Denis, 1958</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Denis, 1958" authorityName="Denis" authorityYear="1958" box="[1060,1359,546,571]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscimanus">
<emphasis box="[1060,1217,547,571]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">E. fuscimanus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Denis, J." box="[1224,1359,546,570]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="81 - 120" refId="ref50398" refString="Denis, J. (1958) Araignees (Araneidea) de l'Afghanistan. I. Videnskabelige Meddelelser fra Dansk naturhistorike Forenning, 120, 81 - 120." type="journal article" year="1958">Denis, 1958</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Moradmand and Jager, 2012" authorityName="Moradmand and Jager" authorityYear="2012" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesopotamicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">E. mesopotamicus</emphasis>
Moradmand and 
<bibRefCitation author="Jager, P." box="[521,649,582,607]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="37 - 57" refId="ref51040" refString="Jager, P. (2012) Revision of the genus Sinopoda Jager, 1999 in Laos with discovery of first eyeless huntsman spider species (Sparassidae: Heteropodinae). Zootaxa, 3415, 37 - 57." type="journal article" year="2012">Jäger, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(for full descriptions, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Moradmand, M. &amp; Jager, P." box="[943,1256,582,607]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="2439 - 2496" refId="ref51693" refString="Moradmand, M. &amp; Jager, P. (2012 a) Taxonomic revision of the huntsman spider genus Eusparassus Simon, 1903 (Araneae: Sparassidae) in Eurasia. Journal of Natural History, 46, 39 - 40, 2439 - 2496." type="journal article" year="2012">Moradmand &amp; Jäger 2012a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="68" pageNumber="69" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="68.[151,1436,438,643]" box="[199,1117,618,643]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,618,643]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Distribution.</emphasis>
From the Middle East to Central and parts of South Asia (
<figureCitation box="[1007,1104,618,642]" captionStart="FIGURE 72" captionStartId="104.[151,250,1968,1991]" captionTargetBox="[213,1363,195,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-41@104.[212,1363,195,1942]" captionTargetPageId="104" captionText="FIGURE 72. Distribution range of (a) Eusparassus doriae group; (b) Eusparassus incertae sedis and Cercetius perezi. (a, b) with the same scale." pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Fig. 72a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="68.[151,617,715,741]" box="[151,617,715,741]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,617,715,741]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Species with unclear group affiliation</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="68.[151,1436,786,1062]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
The following three species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pocock, 1901)" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[479,881,786,810]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xerxes">
<emphasis box="[479,699,787,810]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Eusparassus xerxes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pocock, R. I." box="[715,873,786,810]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="478 - 498" refId="ref52017" refString="Pocock, R. I. (1901) Descriptions of some new species of spiders from British India. Journal of Bombay Natural History Society, 13, 478 - 498." type="journal article" year="1901">Pocock, 1901</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Caporiacco, 1935" authorityName="Caporiacco" authorityYear="1935" box="[894,1198,786,810]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontii">
<emphasis box="[894,991,787,810]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">E. pontii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Caporiacco, L. di" box="[1000,1198,786,810]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" refId="ref49970" refString="Caporiacco, L. di. (1935) Aracnidi dell'Himalaia e del Karakoram, raccolti dalla Missione italiana al Karakoram (1929 - VII). Memoire della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 13,161 - 263." type="book" year="1935">Caporiacco, 1935</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Simon, 1902" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Cercetius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perezi">
<emphasis box="[1254,1436,787,811]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Cercetius perezi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Simon, E." box="[151,295,822,846]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="252 - 254" refId="ref52657" refString="Simon, E. (1902) Arachnides recueillis au cours de la Mission de MM. J. Bonnier et Ch. Perez au Golfe Persique (Mars - Avril 1901). Bulletin du Museum d'historie naturelle (Paris), 8, 252 - 254." type="journal article" year="1902">Simon, 1902</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be placed in the species groups recognized above. They show a transition in character states. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Caporiacco" authorityYear="1935" box="[151,365,859,882]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontii">
<emphasis box="[151,365,859,882]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Eusparassus pontii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely allied to the members of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[816,889,859,883]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doriae">
<emphasis box="[816,889,859,883]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">doriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group but differ from them by having a distinct dark marking on the ventral opisthosoma (
<figureCitation box="[639,736,894,918]" captionStart="FIGURE 56" captionStartId="88.[151,250,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,194,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-74@88.[151,1436,193,1813]" captionTargetPageId="88" captionText="FIGURE 56. Habitus and ventral views of Eusparassus spp. (a) Eusparassus educatus spec. nov. paratype male from Namibia; (b) Eusparassus tuckeri (Lawrence, 1927) comb. nov., female from Namibia; (c–d) Eusparassus xerxes (Pocock, 1901) (c syntype male from Pakistan, d syntype subadult male from Iran); (e–f) Eusparassus pontii Caporiacco, 1935, female from Ladakh, Himalayas, India." pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Fig. 56f</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Caporiacco" authorityYear="1935" box="[756,972,895,918]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontii">
<emphasis box="[756,972,895,918]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Eusparassus pontii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[1182,1286,895,918]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xerxes">
<emphasis box="[1182,1286,895,918]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">E. xerxes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(presence of ventral opisthosoma marking) but differs by having a single bristle instead of four at the basal segment of the chelicerae. This species is probably derived from the members of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[972,1045,966,990]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doriae">
<emphasis box="[972,1045,966,990]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">doriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group in the Himalayas. For full description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Caporiacco" authorityYear="1935" box="[317,415,1003,1026]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontii">
<emphasis box="[317,415,1003,1026]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">E. pontii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Moradmand, M. &amp; Jager, P." box="[476,793,1002,1027]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="2439 - 2496" refId="ref51693" refString="Moradmand, M. &amp; Jager, P. (2012 a) Taxonomic revision of the huntsman spider genus Eusparassus Simon, 1903 (Araneae: Sparassidae) in Eurasia. Journal of Natural History, 46, 39 - 40, 2439 - 2496." type="journal article" year="2012">Moradmand &amp; Jäger 2012a</bibRefCitation>
. The distribution of these three species is shown in 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 72" captionStartId="104.[151,250,1968,1991]" captionTargetBox="[213,1363,195,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-41@104.[212,1363,195,1942]" captionTargetPageId="104" captionText="FIGURE 72. Distribution range of (a) Eusparassus doriae group; (b) Eusparassus incertae sedis and Cercetius perezi. (a, b) with the same scale." pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Fig. 72b</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
